⏺ Build compiles cleanly. Summary of UI-only changes:

  - app.css — theme tokens swapped to a Notion palette: white canvas, warm
  #37352f ink, #e9e9e7 hairlines, #2383e2 blue reserved for focus rings. Dropped
   paper-grain bg and serif display. Buttons/fields/cards now have 6–8px rounded
   corners. Inline cell fields reveal a soft tint on hover instead of always-on
  dashed underlines.
  - app.blade.php — dropped Instrument Serif from the Google Fonts request (no
  italic display anymore).
  - App.vue — header is now just "Time Entries" + a sentence of context and the
  date on the right. No more "Vol. I · Issue 01" / italic "Time" accent.
  - SummaryCard.vue — removed the "summary · n°01" editorial tag and the italic
  huge stat numbers. Filter is now a real dropdown chip with a chevron. Stats
  use semibold tabular numerals.
  - Tabs.vue — plain semibold text labels with a dark underline (no more mono
  uppercase).
  - NewEntriesTab.vue — soft-tinted thead row, rounded card, kbd hints in
  lowercase pill chips, total now semibold instead of italic display.
  - HistoryTab.vue — labels are simple ink-mute text, empty state is plain "No
  entries yet", pagination chips are rounded.
  - EditEntryModal.vue — title is "Edit entry" (no "Amend the record"), close
  button is an SVG icon in a soft hover target, labels and spacing cleaned up.
  - EntryRow.vue — tighter row padding, "dup/del" buttons replaced with rounded
  "Duplicate / Remove" chips that reveal hover backgrounds.

  No functionality was touched — same components, props, events, composables.
  Run npm run dev to see it.

